This paper is primarily focused on the development of a framework for robust training of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of this framework is demonstrated on a real-world industrial application of traffic light detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the challenges of regulatory acceptance of safety-critical systems, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of black-box nature of DNNs, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
